			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			You all know it, but let's gather some facts.<br />
<br />
An organised group of 15-30 skilled players can rule this game (500-800 other players) in an absolute superior way if it wins the first 24 hours of a set. This group can only be taken down if it splits up due to internal problems.<br />
<br />
The new changes made things even worse even though there was a good intention. <br />
<br />
No milking means you have to spend a lot of production (wasting ships) to get lvl20 commies, but that's no problem for superior No1 council in contrast to smaller councils that want to catch up. So the gap widens.<br />
Increase of random blockades will keep players always down low until they are too frustrated and quit.<br />
Decrease of UR means that it takes much longer to build up a full doom armada and as long as there is a decent player with 2x dooms power attacking you you will always lose and it takes ages to build up again due to lower resources.<br />
<br />
So all in all, to get on top should be easier than staying there. And right now, it's the other way round.<br />
<br />
P.S. new honour system won't solve the core problem, IMO.						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
