				posted 2004-08-25 19:49&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=8914"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=8906"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	[QUOTE]Exactly. And I semi remember the comment a while ago that TE made about coordinating this whole take-over in the beginning over a period of weeks. Was I the only one that thought that was just a LITTLE over the top? [/QUOTE]<br />
<br />
Well, maybe it was a bit over the top but if TE hadn't done it koreans would have dominated again exactly like last set. <br />
<br />
IMO the problem with the game is, as Keyan said before, that the powerful councils will become even more powerful, while the weak councils stay weak. With the recent updates this has even be forced. That's why the beginning is so important. Once you are #1 you'll stay there till the end of the set. <br />
<br />
I think it would be better to give weak players benefits than to limit some things (like commie milking, planet production, fusion) for everyone.<br />
In Archspace you can fall very fast. Between being top 10 and being dead there often are just a couple of minutes. But it doesn't work the other way around. Rising in power is very difficult and often impossible due to the reasons everyone knows. <br />
In Order to make the game less frustrating there are only two possiblites (IMO). Either include some kind of protection if you've lost too much power or speed up the rebuilding process. Personally I don't like the idea of protection, because it's another limitation. Better give weak player production boosts while giving players with strong fleets production penalties. Give players the opportunity to get enough lvl 20 commanders in a short time no matter what power they have. This way there will be much more fleetbattles in the game. Especially new players will have no chance to learn the game, if they never get the chance to test designs, weapons, formations and commander abilites. The only way to learn this stuff is in fleet battles so ppl should have the opportunity to war often. <br />
<br />
Also the beginning of the reset is less important because when ppl can rebuild faster they can achieve much more with coordination later in game. This way it'll be challenging both, for the #1 council and for the other councils. Saying TE,koreans,AZG or whoever is ruining the gameplay always is the easiest conclusion. <br />
<br />
My 20 cent ;)<br />
~Ziu(TE|retired)			   <P align=right></P>
