			  	I really tried to avoid the name TE, cause it doesn't matter, as it was said before it could have been Koreans or any other organised and skilled force, like sets before this year.<br />
You can't blame a council to strive for No1 by all possible means the game provides.<br />
<br />
So, let's try to carry on this discussion on a neutral point of view.<br />
<br />
As Ziu said I also think it might be worth to think about some penalties the more powerful your empire becomes, something like &quot;corruption&quot; may be. <br />
Moreover, I think planet power needs to be increased.<br />
In any case, there's no point to bring down No1 council by Empire attacks or random destructive events. That wouldnt be good for the game either.<br />
I would rather like to see players to try bringing down No1 council through real fleet battles. <br />
<br />
-Keyan (TE)			   <P align=right></P>
