				<IMG src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/posticon.gif" border=0>
				posted 2004-08-25 21:20&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=8919"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=8906"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	While I do agree that taking down the council is often very hard, it is by no means impossible...<br />
<br />
However, I do agree that some steps might be appropriate....<br />
<br />
I do not think that allowing milking or some other unfair advantage to weak players is the correct solution though.. In addition, making planets have more power will achieve the exact opposite of your objectives, since then the player's total power will be less affected by his ships, effectively allowing players with even MORE ships to hit players with even LESS ships then before...<br />
Instead, I propose this:<br />
<br />
* The primary objective is to make it harder on the top council to stay on top. as of now, once a council has achieved a certain power advantege over all other councils, the workload of staying in this advantage is severely lessened.<br />
<br />
* To achieve this goal, The empire needs to become more agressive - feeling threatened from strong players, It should ask for more and more money more and more often, the more powerfull someone becomes... In addition to money, It should ask players to attack other players it doesnt like.<br />
<br />
* Of course, if the empire doesnt like someone, and no one agrees to attack him, it will do do the dirty work itself, attacking him, and if winning, keeping his planets...<br />
<br />
* Because of the new agressiveness of the empire, its initiale planets should be reduced to a couple  hundreds.. the reason is so that resets can be shorter and dont prolonge for a huge time after everyone has finished researching... the resets will not be very short though, because after all, the empire can be the agressor...<br />
<br />
* this should be imposed on everyone, but of course, it will hurt more to whoever is very powerfull - as in real life - even with all the technological advances, spaceships should decay with time. its Illogical that a ship can be used for very long without maintenance, and eventually, it should get scrapped... <br />
 * what I propose is that even ships that werent damaged must be repaired after some time/X battles (whatever comes first), with the time between maintenances shortening as the ship ages, shortening faster as the ship participates in battles, and even faster when it gets damaged.<br />
 * as the ship ages it cannot stay as efficient as it was, when it just came off the production line... and when a ship gets damaged in battle, no matter the amount of repair done, there is alwasys some permenant damage...<br />
 * when the ship has decay reaches critical levels, the ship must be either scrapped, or risk exploding in battlefield, wrecking havoc on all nearby ships, or at home, destroying other ships, and maybe damaging or destroying planets on the way... maybe a ship should just have a small chance to explode every turn, and as the ship ages and gets damaged, the % should increase...<br />
<br />
* In conjunction with the aging ships, its also illogical that commanders live forever... <br />
 * I propose that commanders should also age, they abilities first increasing as they become wiser etc, and then decrasing as they become old and lose their quick thinking etc.. of course, they should eventually die...<br />
 * In addition, its not probable that If a commander does nothing for a long time, hell stay just as fit as he were... to stay in top shape, the commanders need to train, and also have battles, although not as frequent as trining... the frequency should increase with the experiance of the commander, lvl 20 commanders being an elite of elite, and having to train almost 24/7 and battle constantly to not lose their edge... if a commander doesnt train/go to battle for a certain duration, there should be some exp. decay... after all, lvl 20 it the top of the top of the elite commanders, and how many top elite can you have? :D<br />
<br />
I think the most important changes are the ship and commander decay in that order, which will ensure that being extra super huge is extremely hard :P to make matters more interesting, its possible to do the changes with the empire (btw, I was told that the empire IS aggressive now (ive been away from the game for a while...))<br />
<br />
a very radical change that could be tried is making no limit for how high up can be researched,  (i.e. having 'special' research after the normal one is finished, and you ascended :D) and for the power of the weapons and other ship utilities which can be manufactured... this way, weak people can concentrate on research, and beat the top guys using superior technology...<br />
<br />
This last change just came to me, so I wrote it in case anyone finds it an interesting proposition... I havent thought it over much, and it might turn out that it doesnt achieve what I was looking for, so more consideration is needed here...			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
		  </TR>

		
