				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=8922"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=8906"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	I have a bit of a different opinion about the blockade... I dont know if it should be cancelled outside of a war - I need to consider that for a while - but I think that both blockage and siege screens provide you with too much free information - Its understandable that the planet's size, and most attributes could be seen even from clusters away, but stuff like its resources, or wether it has hostile aliens, violent microbes, volcanos etc.. might be a little too much...<br />
this info should be gathered by spying. Maybe this way, spying modifiers will be a bit more usefull important, other then for stealing techs, and it will be harder to hunt for URs if you have a bad spying ability (and in general, becuase it costs money to spy, youre not always successfull, etc..)<br />
this will also help against one giant council overtaking the game, since if good planets are hard to find, top councils wont have that huge an advantage as now... and security levels would also mean something after the tech race is over...<br />
<br />
actually, thinking about it, this is probably the easiest feature to implement, (not show all info on siege/block screen) and it will have an impact almost as strong as the other measures I suggested...			   <P align=right></P>
