			  	Ziu - The limiting factor on the Empire can be put differently, for example, the top 15 councils will be targeted. It does not neccessary have to attack someone just because of the power that 1 council process. That way, the top council must constantly build up in order to counter the aggressiveness of the Empire, and then the weaker concils can strive to take them down in a coalition of some sort.<br />
<br />
As for the decaying ships, that is actually a pretty good idea. As the ship ages, its abilities will be decreased over time. But this, however, will take days, hell, even weeks to implement into the system, so the suggestion must be considered very by the mods.<br />
<br />
For blockading, look at examples from WWI, WWII, the Berlin Blockade and the Cuban Missle Crisis. Isn't blockading something to limit the supply of the enemy? So Nova's suggestion, making blockade a war act, would stand, but destroying the entire fleet of the enemy would be unlikely because the aggressor's fleet would not be engaged unless the defender's fleet strength is greater than the aggressor's. The Recon idea is a pretty good one too, making it neccessary to use the spy option.<br />
<br />
My comment on the recent suggestions.<br />
<br />
Neo_Blitzkrieg,<br />
Bringer of the Red Guards			   <P align=right></P>
