			  	As a new player to THIS game I will give my opinion. TE is ruining the game for me (thats said). However no one in the above or this post is saying they are or have done anything illegal to get to the top spot (congrats to you). They took full advantage of the game as it is currently played. So here is my opinion of a few changes:<br />
<br />
1) NO ALLIED FLEET- This I will explain later<br />
<br />
2) No in council war ever. (Planet passing to the top member)<br />
<br />
3) All wars between 2 council would concluded after X hours and could not be restarted between the same councils for X time.<br />
<br />
4) Let the defensive player have the option of defending a blockade by a much superior player in power. The fleets station on planets defend against raid and privateering and seiges.<br />
<br />
5) Stop multi's, stop multi's, stop multi's<br />
<br />
6) Since I know someone is thinking get your sister council to seige and blockade you with crap fleet to train commies. Each ATTACK you lose after the first one to the same player (within a certain time frame) would take away from your commies confidence and abilities unless you attacked with X percent their power.<br />
<br />
7) If you declare independence from a council after the council have started a war you can never go back. For 48 hours you can still be attacked as if you were a member of the council you left.<br />
<br />
8) 2 request per set to join different council. After that you are there for the remainer of the set.<br />
<br />
There are others but this is it for now. IF you think everything is crazy that is and opinion also. But do take a close look at my reasoning for no allied fleet.<br />
<br />
Now to explain the NO ALLIED FLEET. With no allied fleet to protect you it become difficult for member of the super councils to break away and rape other councils. This will stop a player with 500k in power from breaking away from their council with 3 players with 60K and attacking a council with 12 player and each player is averaging 60K in power. With no allied fleet to support them it is like 3 against 12. <br />
<br />
Reasoning: In our war with (cough) we managed to kill a high ranking player (with the empires help). Within 8 hours that player was back with his foot in our rears and at approximately 1.3mil in power and 79 planets. With no allied fleet that player would not survive a come back during combat. For this player to survive you would have call a truce. In a war ONLY ONLY ONLY the superior council can support weaker members with allied fleet.<br />
<br />
Coding nightmare maybe but it is my opinion. I wonder how many names I will be called for this one? Excuse all spelling error.<br />
