			  	edead - of course the game is under constant change - I have not for one second, thought otherwise... :D<br />
needless to say that abusable features should not be incorporated into the game... the feedback I was looking for was for my ideas, to make them better so that I will post them on the suggestions board in a complete state (that is if i generally see people agree to them)...<br />
<br />
keyan - same thing edead said, plus, if you dont think these changes can work, drop a few suggestions of your own... but dont ask for exploitable features please :D<br />
<br />
ziu - what I see you do is just dismiss everything suggested... not only do you not give any other suggestions of what to do instead, but you put no thought or effort whatsoever into you dismissals...<br />
<br />
&quot;Empire targets top 15 councils<br />
--&gt; #1 council will split in 15+ subs with 2 players in each.&quot;<br />
<br />
small councils can only go to war with small councils - and if the players will be strong, they wont be able to find councils of their size with players of their size... and besides, if the top council can do it, so can everyone - and since the top council's players are the strongest, they will still be on top and get attacked... only now they will only be able to give 2 total support fleets to each other...<br />
<br />
&quot;Decaying Ships<br />
--&gt; Players with high production can easily replace those ships with new ones. Once you are #1 it isn't difficult to build a new doomstar armada every 1-2 days.&quot;<br />
<br />
thats right, only you forgot one thing - the more ships the player builds and lets decay, the more chance of some of them exploding and destroying other fleets, etc... and the decayed fleets also dont fight as well... anyway, the point is, that unlike now where players can have and upkeep thousands of doomstars, even hundreds will be hard to keep for long... and as the numbers increase, part of the ships is constantly going to be in maintenance... enabling smaller players to more easily bite through...<br />
<br />
combined with the empire giving them a hard time, staying on top wont be picnic...<br />
<br />
&quot;Decaying Commanders<br />
--&gt; They can be replaced very easy aswell. When you are #1 you can train many lvl20 commanders every day.&quot;<br />
<br />
werent you the one who kept whining that without milking, its next to impossible to get good commanders now? do you think those 2m players on top have many target to blockade? because I dont... this already breaks a part of your story - either the top guys wont have many good commanders because of no one to attack, or they will be closer in power to the rest, meaning my theory has worked, but enabling them to get good commanders... anyway, by blockading its very hard to get more then 1-2 lvl 20's in a day, (and thats assuming you always win and have no losses...) unless most of the battles are very large scale, meaning the enemy has a lot of firepower, meaning part of my goals were met :D win-win :P<br />
<br />
&quot;Blockading only when you are at war<br />
--&gt; #1 council will simply stay in permanent war with everyone.&quot;<br />
its kinda hard to stay in permenant war with everyone, unless they have similar council power - otherwise they cant declare... and if council powers are close, my goal is achieved :D<br />
<br />
<br />
&quot;Use empire to hit players with much power<br />
--&gt; Unless they give the empire commanders uber-stats it won't be a problem to defend. Against the empire and most players you can win even full doomstar battles without losses.<br />
And if you give the empire uber-stats, well, if you bring down the #1 council the empire will destroy the next #1 council so at the end ppl will try to avoid being ranked high. Don't think that would be fun.&quot;<br />
<br />
first of all, people will always try to rank high..<br />
second, the empire will not kill the top council or even the top players, but it will hurt them...<br />
with the ship decay and commander decay it will not be so easy to withstand an empire's hit with no consequences... also remember that to defend from the empire, one needs fleets at home - so top players wont be able to smash their whole armadas at the people they attack now - they would have to keep around half at home to defend from the empire, allowing the weak guys to decently defend...<br />
<br />
&quot;Disable seeing planet features<br />
--&gt; #1 council simply takes all planets from a player and destroys the crap. &quot;<br />
<br />
by also taking the crap, the players bloat their power without increasing capacity that much - so they would have to do the killing rounds slowly, in 12 hour rounds, allowing for MUCH more competition in the way... I wont get too much into this now, but If you consider top councils' strategies, they all focus on UR hunting... by not showing them everything right away, their whole strategy collapses...<br />
<br />
ziu, I dont really undertand what you are trying to achieve... do you want to log on about once a day for about an hour and take down the top council every time? no baby! of course you have to work for it... but right now, to take down a top council, you must be way better then them - in a totally different league... with the improvements, really good players will be able to take down really good players...<br />
<br />
all in all, my suggestions are not meant to destroy the guy on top, and even with the changes its very likely that councils would be able to hold out for a week and more if very good, but overall staying on top will be harder, and the top council will be more in reach for destruction by the the midweight guy... It does not mean, however that he will get to be on top, because the top will always be reserved for the more coordinating, more thoughtful, skillfull, and with the more time on their hands :D<br />
