			  	LOL, Psycholis, sounds like you have taken some chemistry classes in your life. Thats the kind of thing you learn about in high school chem, and more in University (I am majoring in Chem right now). The problem with entropy, is that the world and indeed the whole universe is becoming more and more disorganised as time passes. In fact, things which you think are making it more ordered (eg, turning a gas into a solid), are actually increasing the entropy, because of the processes you do in order to create less disorder in an object. <br />
<br />
Houston<br />
<br />
PS, its good for all you kids who need an excuse for why you leave a mess, or shouldn't clean your room. (&quot;I'm sorry mom/dad but because of the laws of entropy, my room tends to evolve to more ad more disorder and I can't stop it&quot;)			   <P align=right></P>
